    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jc.00467_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1878-04-04" rend="right">April 4th 1878</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute></salute>
            </opener>

            <p><gap reason="damage" extent="4 or 5 words" quantity="15" unit="chars"/> glad to hear that <gap reason="damage" extent="1 words" quantity="10" unit="chars"/> thing bother &amp; hope that you will soon be able to come down again &amp; stay with us a week or two.<ptr target="n0817"/> Debbie<ptr target="n0844"/> wants to <choice><sic>se</sic><corr>see</corr></choice> you for something very particular &amp; wishes <choice><orig>evry</orig><reg>every</reg></choice> day that Mr. Whitman would come down. we all want to <choice><sic>se</sic><corr>see</corr></choice> you so much dont wait to get well f <choice><sic>befor</sic><corr>before</corr></choice> you come we will take good care of you here.</p>
            
            <p>George<ptr target="n0852b"/> is <choice><sic>buisy</sic><corr>busy</corr></choice> planting potatoes &amp; <choice><sic>geting</sic><corr>getting</corr></choice> ready for corn planting he is trying to get his work a long while he has such good help <gap reason="damage" extent="3 words" quantity="12" unit="chars"/></p>
           
            <p><gap reason="damage" extent="5 words" quantity="20" unit="chars"/> love to <gap reason="damage" extent="2 words" quantity="7" unit="chars"/></p>
            <closer>
                <signed>SM Stafford</signed>
            </closer>
            
